tool_description: The API is scraping the Wikipedia pages for cats in order to collect data
title: Cat breeds

api_list.name: Group breed data by property
api_list.description: This endpoint will group the available data by the given property and the property value. The property can be any property of the JSON response object including the properties of the meta object.
api_list.code:
import requests

url = "https://cat-breeds.p.rapidapi.com/cat_breeds/group/{property}/{property_value}"

headers = {
    "X-RapidAPI-Key": "SIGN-UP-FOR-KEY",
    "X-RapidAPI-Host": "cat-breeds.p.rapidapi.com"
}

response = requests.get(url, headers=headers)

print(response.json())

api_list.name: Get Breed Information
api_list.description: This endpoint will return information for a specific cat breed
api_list.code:
import requests

url = "https://cat-breeds.p.rapidapi.com/cat_breeds/breed/{breed}"

headers = {
    "X-RapidAPI-Key": "SIGN-UP-FOR-KEY",
    "X-RapidAPI-Host": "cat-breeds.p.rapidapi.com"
}

response = requests.get(url, headers=headers)

print(response.json())

api_list.name: Get All Cat Breeds
api_list.description: This endpoint will return back all available cat breeds that are available
api_list.code:
import requests

url = "https://cat-breeds.p.rapidapi.com/cat_breeds"

headers = {
    "X-RapidAPI-Key": "SIGN-UP-FOR-KEY",
    "X-RapidAPI-Host": "cat-breeds.p.rapidapi.com"
}

response = requests.get(url, headers=headers)

print(response.json())
